AOZORA BANK,LTD. Revenue and Financial Data

   Aozora Bank hopes that the clouds have passed and blue skies are ahead. Aozora (which means blue sky in Japanese) was the second Japanese credit bank nationalized in the wake of Asia's financial crisis (after Shinsei Bank). Bad loans and Japan's "Big Bang" financial deregulation added to its troubles. Now a full-service commercial bank, Aozora has some 20 branches in Japan and three offices overseas (New York, Shanghai, and Singapore). It provides a host of retail and business banking services, as well as corporate banking services (loans and derivative products, consulting and advisory) and specialty finance and financial markets offerings. Aozora is seeking to expand in Southeast Asia, particularly Indonesia.
  







